<HEAD>$Adv07</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, May 7, and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>Examples of Honesty Test Questions</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Also on financial wire</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Testing Workers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are sample questions from integrity and substance-abuse
tests, designed and marketed by Las Vegas-based Lousig-Nont &amp;
Associates Inc.:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _Which type of merchandise have you taken, without permission of
the owner, from a place where you have worked? (Mark only one.)
   a. Minor office supplies; pen, pencil, envelope, paper clip, etc.
   b. Small inepensive things; book, magazine, cigarettes, etc.
   c. Small expensive things; tape recorder, radio, jewelry, etc.
   d. Large expensive things; microwave oven, stereo, etc.
   e. Nothing at all.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _Most people who have stolen something from work generally have
a reason for doing what they did. Some reasons are better than
others. People who have never stolen anything have reasons for the
way they are too. Which statement below best describes why you feel
the way you do? (Mark only one.)
   a. Everyone else was stealing. I got pressured into it. I know
it was dumb and it won't happen again.
   b. My financial problems were so great that I couldn't stand the
pressure.
   c. My parents taught me stealing is wrong no matter what. I
wouldn't be able to sleep at night.
   d. My employer was really unfair and the pay was rotten. I only
stole what the company owed me.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _When was the last time you were present when drugs were being
purchased or sold, even though you may not have been involved
yourself?
   a. Refuse to answer
   b. This month
   c. Within 12 months
   d. over 2 years
   e. over 10 years
   f. I never have
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End adv for Sunday, May 7</NOTE>
